songs.title: LeeAnne
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I beg that you read, 'cause I don't know where to start
Though we never met, I know who you really are
Three in the morning and I should be asleep
I'm lying in bed, watching you sing to me

[Pre-Chorus]
I love you, oh, you're so perfect
You must feel this too
I'm waiting on your intermission
You and I will be together soon

[Chorus]
Lee Anne holds me again
Lee Anne, you’re my biggest fan
Yet I know that this needle in my heart [?]
I'm feeling your true love
Lee Anne

[Verse 2]
Do you even care, can you never hold back?
Now that you're famous, mister too-cool-for-that
My boyfriend got jealous that I got your name tattooed
He don't understand me the way that you do

[Pre-Chorus]
I love you, oh, you're so perfect
You must feel this too
I'm waiting on your intermission
You and I will be together soon

[Chorus]
Lee Anne holds me again
Lee Anne, you’re my biggest fan
Yet I know that this needle in my heart [?]
I'm feeling your true love
Lee Anne

[Instrumental Bridge]

[Chorus]
Lee Anne
Lee Anne holds me again
I'm feeling your true love
Lee Anne
